There is nothing in the NYSDOT map that indicates this intersection is part of the I-87 High Occupancy Toll (HOT) HOV/GOV route. I did a search and found it does not appear on the New York State Thruway (NYS TR) map that is used by NJ TRANSIT, but it does appear on the USGS topogrpah (TTG) map of the Hudson River and Catskill Mountains. This is interesting because the DOT has been trying to reallocate traffic away from this intersection for a long time without success. In the mid 1990s they proposed renaming it, but that was nixed by Gov. Mario Cuomo as a cost of doing business in his plan to privatize the state highway system. Since then it has been inoperable due to damage from Hurricane Sandy in 2012 that knocked out power and caused traffic snarls all over the tri-state area.


